    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>GERMAN-CANADIAN TRUCK DEAL</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Timothy Pritchard</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Pritchard, Timothy</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Germany's DaimlerChrysler AG agrees to buy Western Star Trucks Holdings of Kelowna, British Columbia, for 670 million Canadian dollars ($456 million) and merge it into its Freightliner truck division (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The German auto giant DaimlerChrysler A.G. agreed to buy Western Star Trucks Holdings of Kelowna, British Columbia, for 670 million Canadian dollars ($456 million) and merge it into its Freightliner truck division. Western Star, which makes heavy trucks in Kelowna and transit buses in Mississauga, Ontario, and Oriskany, N.Y., had sales last year of $885 million, less than one-tenth of those of Freightliner.</p>
        <p>Timothy Pritchard</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
